<div class="space-y-6">

  <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Sajdah Ayahs</h2>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
    QUL exports Sajdah data(list of ayah where Sajdah is prescribed) in both <strong>JSON</strong> and <strong>SQLite</strong> formats.
    Each record includes the ayah key, sajdah number, and whether the sajdah is <em>optional</em> or <em>required</em>.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mt-4">Sample JSON</h3>
  <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre overflow-x-auto">
    {
    "1": {
    "sajdah_number": 1,
    "verse_key": "7:206",
    "sajdah_type": "optional"
    }
    }
  </div>

  <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mt-4">Field Descriptions</h3>
  <div class="tools-table-overflow">
    <table class="min-w-full text-sm text-left border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
      <thead class="bg-gray-100 text-xs uppercase font-semibold">
      <tr>
        <th class="px-4 py-2">Field</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-2">Type</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-2">Description</th>
      </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
      <tr>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">sajdah_number</td>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">Integer</td>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">Sequential number of the sajdah verse</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">verse_key</td>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">String</td>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">Reference to the verse in the format <code>surah:ayah</code> (e.g., <code>7:206</code>)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">sajdah_type</td>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">String</td>
        <td class="px-4 py-2">
          Type of sajdah:
          <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
            <li><code>required</code> – Sujood is obligatory upon recitation or hearing</li>
            <li><code>optional</code> – Sujood is recommended</li>
          </ul>
        </td>
      </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

</div>
